intaining data integrity.\\n' +\n        'FR-03 \\tAutomated\\n' +\n        'Scheduling\\n' +\n        'Functional \\tThe system must automatically\\n' +\n        'calculate the next trip time based\\n' +\n        'University Transport Management System - Lab 3 Report - Page 2',\n      num: 2\n    },\n    {\n      text: 'on historical data and driver\\n' +\n        'availability.\\n' +\n        'NFR-01 Latency &\\n' +\n        'Response Time\\n' +\n        'Non-Functional \\tThe map must refresh the location\\n' +\n        'within 5 seconds. This defines the\\n' +\n        'quality of service (Performance)\\n' +\n        'rather than a specific feature.\\n' +\n        'NFR-02 Cross-Platform\\n' +\n        'Compatibility\\n' +\n        'Non-Functional \\tThe application must maintain\\n' +\n        '100% feature parity across\\n' +\n        'Android, iOS, and Web browsers\\n' +\n        '(Usability/Portability).\\n' +\n        'NFR-03 GDPR/Data\\n' +\n        'Privacy\\n' +\n        'Compliance\\n' +\n        'Non-Functional \\tDefines legal and security\\n' +\n        'constraints on how student travel\\n' +\n        'history is stored and purged\\n' +\n        '(Security).\\n' +\n        '3. REQUIREMENT PRIORITIZATION\\n' +\n        'Prioritization ensures that the development team focuses on high-value\\n' +\n        'features first. We use a scoring model based on Business Value (BV),\\n' +\n        'Technical Feasibility (TF), and Overall Importance (OI) on a scale of 1-10.\\n' +\n        '• Priority 1: Real-time Bus Tracking (OI: 10/10)\\n' +\n        'BV: 10 | TF: 8\\n' +\n        'Reasoning: This is the \"Must-Have\" requirement. Without tracking,\\n' +\n        'the UTMS offers no competitive advantage over a physical paper\\n' +\n        'schedule. It provides the highest value to students by reducing wait\\n' +\n        'times.\\n' +\n        '• Priority 2: Admin Control Panel (OI: 9/10)\\n' +\n        'BV: 9 | TF: 9\\n' +\n        'Reasoning: Essential for operational feasibility. The Transport Admin\\n' +\n        'University Transport Management System - Lab 3 Report - Page 3',\n      num: 3\n    },\n    {\n      text: 'needs to be able to input data and manage drivers for the system to\\n' +\n        'function. High feasibility as it uses standard CRUD operations.\\n' +\n        '• Priority 3: Student Authentication & Profiles (OI: 8/10)\\n' +\n        'BV: 7 | TF: 10\\n' +\n        'Reasoning: Necessary for security and personalization (e.g., \"Favorite\\n' +\n        'Routes\"). Very high feasibility using modern OAuth or Jasper\\n' +\n        'frameworks.\\n' +\n        '• Priority 4: Push Notifications for Delays (OI: 7/10)\\n' +\n        'BV: 8 | TF: 7\\n' +\n        'Reasoning: Significant value for user experience. However, it is\\n' +\n        'dependent on the tracking module and reliable external APIs (like\\n' +\n        'Firebase), making it slightly more complex technically.\\n' +\n        '• Priority 5: Historical Analytics Dashboard (OI: 5/10)\\n' +\n        'BV: 6 | TF: 6\\n' +\n        'Reasoning: Useful for University Management for long-term\\n' +\n        'planning, but not required for the day-to-day operation of the\\n' +\n        'transport service. Classified as a \"Should-Have\" or \"Could-Have.\"\\n' +\n        '4. CONFLICT RESOLUTION\\n' +\n        'Conflicts often arise when stakeholders have competing goals. Below are\\n' +\n        'identified inconsistencies in the UTMS requirements and their engineered\\n' +\n        'solutions.\\n' +\n        'University Transport Management System - Lab 3 Report - Page 4',\n      num: 4\n    },\n    {\n      text: 'Conflict 1: Privacy vs. Safety Oversight (Students vs. Management)\\n' +\n        'The Conflict: Management requested continuous \"Check-in\" data to monitor\\n' +\n        'student attendance via bus usage. Students expressed concerns regarding the\\n' +\n        'tracking of their personal movement patterns outside university hours.\